13 2024, is amended to read:
14 77-3903 (1)(a) A notice of lien provided for in the Uniform State
15 Tax Lien Registration and Enforcement Act upon real property shall be
16 presented in the office of the Secretary of State. Such notice of lien
17 shall be transmitted by the Secretary of State to and filed in the office
18 of the register of deeds by the register of deeds of the county or
19 counties in which the real property subject to the lien is situated as
20 designated in the notice of lien. The register of deeds shall enter the
21 notice in the alphabetical state tax lien index, showing on one line the
22 name and residence of the person liable named in such notice, the last
23 four digits of the social security number or the federal tax
24 identification number of such person, the Tax Commissioner's or
25 Commissioner of Labor's serial number of such notice, the date and hour
26 of filing, and the amount due. Such presentments to the Secretary of
27 State may be made by direct input to the Secretary of State's database or
28 by other electronic means. All such notices of lien shall be retained in
29 numerical order in a file designated state tax lien notices, except that
30 in offices filing by the roll form of microfilm or other accessible
-24-

AM2282 AM2282
LB596 LB596
LPB - 02/25/2026 LPB - 02/25/2026
1 durable medium pursuant to section 23-1517.01, the original notices need
2 not be retained. A lien subject to this subsection shall be effective
3 upon real property when filed by the register of deeds as provided in
4 this subsection.
5 (b) A notice of lien provided for in the Uniform State Tax Lien
6 Registration and Enforcement Act upon personal property shall be filed in
7 the office of the Secretary of State. The Secretary of State shall enter
8 the notice in the state's central tax lien index, showing on one line the
9 name and residence of the person liable named in such notice, the last
10 four digits of the social security number or the federal tax
11 identification number of such person, the Tax Commissioner's or
12 Commissioner of Labor's serial number of such notice, the date and hour
13 of filing, and the amount due. Such filings with the Secretary of State
14 may be filed by direct input to the Secretary of State's database or by
15 other electronic means. All such notices of lien shall be retained in
16 numerical order in a file designated state tax lien notices.
17 (2) The uniform fee, payable to the Secretary of State, for
18 presenting for filing, releasing, continuing, or subordinating or for
19 filing, releasing, continuing, or subordinating each tax lien pursuant to
20 the Uniform State Tax Lien Registration and Enforcement Act shall be two
21 times the fee required for recording instruments with the register of
22 deeds as provided in section 33-109. There shall be no fee for the filing
23 of a termination statement. The uniform fee for each county more than one
24 designated pursuant to subdivision (1)(a) of this section shall be the
25 fee required for recording instruments with the register of deeds as
26 provided in section 33-109. The Secretary of State shall remit each fee
