7 Sec. 11. Section 84-1208, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
8 amended to read:
9 84-1208 (1) The administrator may make or cause to be made
10 preservation duplicates of essential records or may designate as
11 preservation duplicates existing copies thereof. A preservation duplicate
12 shall be durable, accurate, complete, and clear and, if made by means of
13 photography, microphotography, photocopying, film, microfilm, optical
14 imagery, or similar processes using an accessible durable medium, shall
15 be prepared in conformity to standards prescribed and approved by the
16 board.
17 (2) A preservation duplicate made by a photographic, photostatic,
18 microfilm, microcard, miniature photographic, optical imagery, or similar
19 process which accurately reproduces or forms an accessible a durable
20 medium for so reproducing the original shall have the same force and
21 effect for all purposes as the original record, whether the original is
22 in existence or not. A transcript, exemplification, or certified copy of
23 such preservation duplicate shall for all purposes be deemed a
24 transcript, exemplification, or certified copy of the original record.
25 (3) No copy of an essential record shall be used as a preservation
26 duplicate unless, under the general laws of the state, the copy has the
27 same force and effect for all purposes as the original record.
28 (4) A medium is accessible if it is able to be retrieved through
29 intellectual, digital, or physical means within institutional or legal
30 parameters.
